# Frontend Development Guidelines

## Component Structure
- All components must be functional components using hooks
- Class components are deprecated and should be migrated
- Use custom hooks to handle complex state and side effects

## Layout Guidelines
- Always use flexbox for layouts
- Grid layouts are not permitted per company policy
- Use flex properties (flex-direction, justify-content, align-items) for component layouts


## Styling Guidelines
- Always use Tailwind classes for styling instead of inline styles or pixel values
- Use Tailwind's default sizing scale for consistent spacing and dimensions
- Avoid hardcoding dimensions with explicit pixel values
- For colors, use Tailwind's color palette instead of hex values